This paper is about multi-agent reinforcement learning (MARL) with networked agents, which involves sequential decision-making in a common environment without the coordination of any central controller. This topic is closely related to several sub-areas of computer science, including multi-agent systems (cs.MA), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), control systems (cs.SY), and robotics (cs.RO). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.MA, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, and cs.RO.
